|CKBStreet Samurai Maintenance|000

|CK0Maintenance applies only to Street Samurai signature hardware. It does not
add integrity wear or fragmentation to ordinary cyberware or another guild's
equipment.|000

|CKBIntegrity|000
|CK0Integrity is physical implant condition. Incoming damage, severe thermal
events, and specific high-load firmware can accumulate wear. Dashboard begins
warning before output is affected. Below 50% integrity, the paired routine's
damage, duration, mitigation, or other output is reduced, but the hardware
continues to function.|000

|CK0The Cortex OS is shared by the entire platform, so poor Cortex integrity
can influence routines that also use another implant. Higher hardware grades
are more durable and lose visible integrity more slowly under comparable wear.
Rin Kade restores signature hardware integrity for active members.|000

|CKBFragmentation|000
|CK0Fragmentation is firmware disorder created by routine use. Above 50%, it
reduces the affected process's effectiveness and produces warnings. Use
defrag <process> to clean one implant or defrag all to service the entire
loadout. Defrag does not repair physical integrity.|000

|CKBAlerts and actions|000
|CK0Dashboard names the process and the required response. PATCH READY uses
patch <process>. ICE INTRUSION uses purge <process>. RUNTIME FAULT uses
reboot <process>. These commands also accept all, but each addresses only its
own issue type. Logs [process] shows recent changes and their causes.|000

|CK0Maintenance commands cannot run while the contract is inactive, and some
require you to be out of combat. A Repair Coprocessor can perform limited
automatic stabilization in severe cases, but it does not replace clinic
repairs or routine defragmentation.|000

|CKBRepair workflow|000
|CK0Start with dashboard. Use the named maintenance command for fragmentation,
patches, ICE, or faults. If integrity is damaged, visit Rin Kade, engage him,
and choose repair for one implant or all damaged signature hardware. Field and
reinforced hardware repair kits can instead restore one process while away from
the clinic. Use repairkit <process_id>; kits cannot be used during combat and
do not affect fragmentation, patches, ICE, faults, or Heat. Use logs afterward
if you need to confirm what changed.|000

|CK0Samrepair is different from all of these tools. It recovers a corrupt or
incomplete guild installation and is not needed after a normal join.|000
